In a “micro” oriented view, we can think
specifically about what happens to a contract

49
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:17,400
at various stages of its existence. Here is
a graph that symbolizes the timeline of a

50
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,870
typical insurance policy.

51
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:27,169
It marks when a policy starts with a premium
payment. Policies that we focus on, such as

52
